pokedexEntries.red: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.
pokedexEntries.blue: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.
pokedexEntries.yellow: A slim and fast swimmer. It slices its prey with its sharp sickles and drinks the body fluids.
pokedexEntries.gold: In the water, it tucks in its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.
pokedexEntries.silver: With sharp claws, this ferocious, ancient Pokémon rips apart prey and sucks their body fluids.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It was able to swim quickly through the water by compactly folding up its razor-sharp sickles.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water-dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water-dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.
pokedexEntries.emerald: Kabutops once swam underwater to hunt for prey. It was apparently evolving from being a water dweller to living on land as evident from changes in its gills and legs.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It swims freely through water. It catches prey with its scythe-like arms and drains the victim's fluids.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains their fluids.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.
pokedexEntries.pearl: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water-dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Kabutops swam underwater to hunt for its prey in ancient times. The Pokémon was apparently evolving from being a water-dweller to living on land as evident from the beginnings of change in its gills and legs.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Its body had begun to change so it could function on land. But it didn’t adapt in time and went extinct.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It swims at speeds of roughly 29 knots, quickly closing in on its prey and slashing into them with its scythes to finish them off.
